readData

public int readData(com.nokia.nfc.nxp.mfstd.MFKey.KeyA key)
Read the complete raw data from the tag, using the specified key. If no key is provided (= null), the default key KEY_BYTES_FF will be used. The contents of the tag are saved to a file, the callback will receive information about the tag.

Parameters:
key - Key A to use for the conneciton. KEY_BYTES_FF (= Mifare default) is used when no key is specified.
Returns:
number of bytes read from the tag.

setDataToWrite

public void setDataToWrite(byte[] data)
Cache the data to write to a tag. Call this first, then writeData().

Parameters:
data - byte array containing the raw tag data to write.

writeData

public boolean writeData(com.nokia.nfc.nxp.mfstd.MFKey.KeyA key)
Write cached data to the tag, using the specified key. Uses the default key KEY_BYTES_FF if no key is specified (= null).

Parameters:
key - Key A to use for the conneciton. KEY_BYTES_FF (= Mifare default) is used when no key is specified.
Returns:
whether writing was successful.
